Varsha Rao,aabhas@myasiavc.com," Varsha Rao serves as Chief Executive Officer & Board Member at Nurx.  Rao is an Angel Investor and Advisor at Ubiquitilink. She served as Chief Operating Officer at Clover Health. She served as Head of Global Operations at Airbnb. She was the Co-Founder and served as the Co-Chief Executive Officer at Eve.com.  Rao served as Senior Vice President of International at LivingSocial.  Rao oversaw LivingSocial's international businesses across Asia, Europe, Australia, New Zealand, and Latin America. She formerly served as CEO of SingTel Digital Media, as VP/GM of Oldnavy.com.  Rao received her Masters of Business Administration from Harvard Business School and received her Bachelor of Science in Economics from The University of Pennsylvania.","United States, California United States, San Francisco California United States, Americas, North America, Northwest, Bay Area",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,"[""Lily AI - $2,000,000 - Seed Round"", ""Directly - $2,750,000 - Seed Round"", ""Deserve - $7,100,000 - Early stage VC"", ""Goodera - $5,500,000 - Early stage VC"", ""Noom - $58,000,000 - Later stage VC"", ""Printify - $3,000,000 - Seed Round"", ""Athelas - $5,500,000 - Seed Round"", ""Dandy - $2,500,000 - Seed Round"", ""Identified - $1,500,000 - Early stage VC"", ""LawnStarter - $1,000,000 - Seed Round"", ""Wonderschool - Seed Round"", ""Custora - Seed Round"", ""Printify - $3,000,000 - Seed Round""]",0,,,,"[""Seed Round"", ""Early stage VC"", ""Later stage VC""]","Marketplaces, Analytics, Internet, SaaS, Technology, Media and Telecom (TMT), E-Commerce, Social Media, Beauty, Mobile, Health & Wellness (LOHAS), AI and Machine Learning, FinTech",,,,https://twitter.com/varsharao,http://sg.linkedin.com/in/varsharao,https://angel.co/varsharao,https://www.varsharao.com/,,Varsha Rao,varsha@nurx.com,+1 (800) 321-6879,"",http://sg.linkedin.com/in/varsharao,https://twitter.com/varsharao,https://angel.co/varsharao,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Ashby Monk,aabhas@myasiavc.com," Ashby Monk is a Co-Founder and Chairman of the Board of Aligned Intermediary. He is also a Co-Founder and Chairman of Long Game. He also serves as Advisor at Addepar. He previously served as Senior Advisor of Special Opportunities at Alberta Investment Management Corporation. He served as an Advisor at Zanbato. He also serves as an Executive and Research Director of the Stanford Global Projects Center, Senior Research Associate at the University of Oxford and Senior Advisor to the Chief Investment Officer at the University of California.","United States, California United States, New York United States, Los Gatos California United States, Los Angeles County California United States, New York New York United States, Americas, North America, Northwest, Great Lakes, New York Metro",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,"[""Index - $7,000,000 - Early stage VC"", ""Ethic - $1,400,000 - Pre Seed"", ""Shelton AI - $50,000 - Pre Seed"", ""Deception And Truth Analysis - $50,000 - Pre Seed"", ""Nfinita - $25,000 - Pre Seed"", ""Enduring Planet - Seed Round"", ""Long Game - $6,600,000 - Seed Round"", ""Kensho - $10,000,000 - Seed Round"", ""Addepar - Pre Seed"", ""Teapot"", ""Real Capital Innovation (Acquired by Addepar) - Seed Round""]",0,,,,"[""Pre Seed"", ""Seed Round"", ""Early stage VC""]","Analytics, Insurance, Health & Wellness (LOHAS), Blockchain, AI and Machine Learning, Finance, Data, FinTech, PropTech, CleanTech",,,,https://twitter.com/sovereignfund,http://www.linkedin.com/pub/ashby-monk/9/a47/208/,http://www.institutionalinvestor.com/Blogs-and-Columns-Ashby-Monks-Avenue-of-Giants.html,https://angel.co/ashby,https://addepar.com/company,Ashby Monk,amonk@stanford.edu,"","",http://www.linkedin.com/pub/ashby-monk/9/a47/208/,https://twitter.com/sovereignfund,http://www.institutionalinvestor.com/Blogs-and-Columns-Ashby-Monks-Avenue-of-Giants.html,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Eric Ewald,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"Established in 2005, Torch Hill Investment Partners, LLC, provides growth capital to domestic and international companies that play vital roles in supply chain integrity, defense, intelligence, civil and corporate security. These companies (1) provide products and services that assist governments in meeting security threats; and (2) provide solutions to corporations that mitigate risks to their physical and critical information assets. The Fund makes both majority and minority investments.","United States, Washington United States, Massachusetts United States, Americas, North America, Northwest",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,[],0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","SaaS, Medical Devices, Manufacturing, Infrastructure, Mobile, Health & Wellness (LOHAS), Telecommunications, IoT, Deep Tech, Defense",,,,https://www.boardwalkcap.com/,,,,,Eric Ewald,eewald@boardwalkcap.com,"","",,,https://www.boardwalkcap.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Adam Wheeler,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"A subsidiary of Massachusetts Mutual Life Insurance Company, Babson Capital is a global investment management organization that manages over $160 billion. The firm has experience in mezzanine and private equity financing and its history dates back to 1940, when the firm was founded in Boston, MA. The firm's transactions are focused on leveraged buy-outs, corporate acquisitions and recapitalizations, with sizes ranging from $25-$300 million. The firm focuses on middle-market companies. Babson's typical investment commitment ranges from $10-$50 million in mezzanine deals and $3-$15 million in private equity investments. Babson recently closed its third mezzanine and private equity fund, Tower Square Capital Partners III, with $1.58 billion in capital commitments. It plans to invest in companies with enterprise values of less than $500 million. With offices in the U.S., Europe, and the Asia Pacific region, Babson makes investments across the globe.","United States, Australia, Missouri United States, North Carolina United States, California United States, Illinois United States, Massachusetts United States, New York United States, Madison County New York United States, Charlotte North Carolina United States, Sydney New South Wales Australia, San Francisco California United States, Springfield Missouri United States, Springfield Massachusetts United States, Chicago Illinois United States, New York New York United States, Oceania, Americas, North America, Northwest, Great Lakes, Bay Area, New York Metro",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,[],0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Professional Services, Industrial Technology, Deep Tech, Transportation",,,,http://www.linkedin.com/in/adamwheeler,,,,,Adam Wheeler,adam.wheeler@investis.com,14804269952,"",http://www.linkedin.com/in/adamwheeler,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Rajesh Sehgal,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"Rajesh Sehgal is an angel investor. Rajesh is currently a Managing Partner at Equanimity Investments, based in Maharashtra, India.","India, Maharashtra India, Asia, South Asia",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,"[""Peel-Works - $790,000 - Seed Round"", ""BabyChakra""]",0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Big Data, AgTech, Technology, Media and Telecom (TMT), E-Commerce, AI and Machine Learning, Finance, FinTech, IoT, Education, HealthTech",,,,http://www.linkedin.com/in/investorrajeshsehgal,https://www.equanimityinvestments.com,,,,Rajesh Sehgal,rajesh@equanimity.vc,+91 (0)98 9230 0104,"",http://www.linkedin.com/in/investorrajeshsehgal,,https://www.equanimityinvestments.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Aniruddha Nazre,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"Dr. Aniruddha Nazre serves as Chairman of the Board at glo. He is an Angel Investor. Ajit Nazre joined Wellington Partners in 2012. He has been working as EVP and CSO at Reliance Industries since 2012. At Reliance, he has been responsible for launching ""Jio"", a Telecom and Digital Media Services venture that can potentially connect 500M Indians to the internet by the end of 2016. Before joining Reliance Ajit was a Senior Partner at Kleiner, Perkins, Caufield & Byers (KPCB) from 2003 to 2011. Ajit made 19 investments with 11 exits. Some of his successful exits at KPCB included LuxVue (acquired by Apple), 3DV (acquired by MSFT), Virsa (acquired by SAP), Vertica (acquired by HP) and InfoEdge (IPO in 2006). Prior to KPCB, he worked at SAP from 1998 to 2003 first as Technical Assistant to Hasso Plattner, CEO, Chairman, and Co-Founder of SAP and later MD of SAPMarkets. Ajit Nazre was the founder SAPMarkets, the e-commerce company that SAP acquired in 2002. Prior to SAP, he worked for six years in the medical device industry. From 1991 till 1995, he worked at Zimmer (then a subsidiary of Bristol Myers Squibb) and from 1995 to 1997 at Mathys AG (Synthes) in Switzerland. He holds seven United States and four European patents and has published and presented over 15 articles in peer-reviewed journals and conferences. He holds a Ph.D. in Biomechanics from the Technical University of Hanover, Germany, an M.S. in Mechanical Engineering from the Michigan Tech, an M.B.A. from the Harvard Business School, and an undergraduate degree in Mechanical Engineering from the College of Engineering Pune, India.","",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,"[""Edge Intelligence (Database Software) - $1,500,000 - Seed Round"", ""Edge Intelligence Software - $1,500,000 - Seed Round""]",0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Big Data, SaaS, Technology, Media and Telecom (TMT), AI and Machine Learning",,,,,,,,,Aniruddha Nazre,"",+1 (408) 598-4400,"",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Salil Donde,aabhas@myasiavc.com," Salil Donde serves as Chief Executive Officer & Board Member at AlphaPoint.  Donde, most recently, was Executive Vice President, Global Information Services at Nasdaq. In this role,  Donde was responsible for leading the strategic direction and overseeing all aspects of the company's Index and Data products businesses which provide solutions, intelligence and insight to the global capital markets.  Donde was instrumental in launching several Machine Learning based products, data products, indexes and sponsored ETFs. Prior to joining Nasdaq,  Donde served as Chief Executive Officer and member of the Board of Directors of Lewtan Technologies, Inc. He has also served as Chief Executive Officer and member of the Board of Directors of Marshall & Swift/Boeckh, and as President of Fiserv Life and Financial Software and Solutions, among the other leadership roles he has held in the broader financial services industry.  Donde received a Bachelor of Technology degree from the Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay","United States, Massachusetts United States, New York United States, New York New York United States, Americas, North America, Great Lakes, New York Metro",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,"[""Lucideus - $1,150,000 - Seed Round"", ""Salil Donde investment in Angel Round - Lucideus - $509,996 - Early stage VC""]",0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Cybersecurity, Technology, Media and Telecom (TMT), Industrial Technology",,,,https://www.linkedin.com/in/salildonde,,,,,Salil Donde,salil@alphapoint.com,+1 (212) 256-1231,"",https://www.linkedin.com/in/salildonde,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
