Carrie Ryan,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"Compass Group Management is an investment advisor to Compass Diversified Holdings (NASDAQ: CODI), as well as to Compass Group Investments Ltd. (CGI), an indirect subsidiary of the Kattegat Trust, a Bermudian trust whose sole beneficiaries are philanthropic entities. The Compass Group's relationship with CGI and Kattegat dates back to 1998 and has spanned a broad range of investments types, including investments in publicly and non-publicly traded equity and debt instruments in U.S. and non-U.S. companies, as well as limited partnership interests in private equity, venture capital and distressed debt funds. CODI seeks to provide its shareholders with superior risk adjusted returns, as well as stable and growing cash distributions, through the acquisition and management of North American middle market businesses (with minimum EBITDA of $8 million). CODI acquires interests in companies in a broad range of industries, with a preferred transaction size of $50 million to $250 million in value.","United States, California United States, Connecticut United States, Westport Connecticut United States, Irvine California United States, Americas, North America, Northwest",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,[],0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Professional Services, Deep Tech",,,,https://www.linkedin.com/in/carrieryancpa/,https://www.compasstrust.com/,,,,Carrie Ryan,carrie@centre-foundation.org,8142376229,"",https://www.linkedin.com/in/carrieryancpa/,,https://www.compasstrust.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Thomas Finke,aabhas@myasiavc.com,"A subsidiary of Massachusetts Mutual Life Insurance Company, Babson Capital is a global investment management organization that manages over $160 billion. The firm has experience in mezzanine and private equity financing and its history dates back to 1940, when the firm was founded in Boston, MA. The firm's transactions are focused on leveraged buy-outs, corporate acquisitions and recapitalizations, with sizes ranging from $25-$300 million. The firm focuses on middle-market companies. Babson's typical investment commitment ranges from $10-$50 million in mezzanine deals and $3-$15 million in private equity investments. Babson recently closed its third mezzanine and private equity fund, Tower Square Capital Partners III, with $1.58 billion in capital commitments. It plans to invest in companies with enterprise values of less than $500 million. With offices in the U.S., Europe, and the Asia Pacific region, Babson makes investments across the globe.","United States, North Carolina United States, Massachusetts United States, New York United States, Madison County New York United States, Charlotte North Carolina United States, Springfield Massachusetts United States, New York New York United States, Americas, North America, Great Lakes, New York Metro",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,[],0,,,,"[""Seed Round""]","Professional Services, Industrial Technology, Deep Tech, Transportation",,,,http://www.linkedin.com/in/tom-finke,,,,,Thomas Finke,tfinke@massmutual.com,14137448411,"",http://www.linkedin.com/in/tom-finke,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Adrian Vanzyl,aabhas@myasiavc.com," Adrian Vanzyl serves as Venture Partner at Wavemaker Partners. He was founding CEO of Ardent Capital in 2011, running the firm for five years from its Bangkok HQ. The venture arm of Ardent was successfully merged into Wavemaker partners in mid 2016, and Adrian joined Wavemaker as Venture Partner. Ardent is one of the most successful operator VCs in Southeast Asia, focusing on eCommerce companies in 7 countries. Adrian continues his role as founding board member of Ardent's key portfolio companies including aCommerce, Orami and Bizzy. Prior to this Adrian was an early stage investor and technologist in the Digital Media space, spending most of his career in Silicon Valley in various venture backed startups. Adrian spent ten years with Bloomberg Capital in San Francisco (most recently as CTO for a $100M early stage digital media focused fund, where he was also CEO of two portfolio companies). Formerly, he was CTO of Sausage Software (and board member at its IPO), CTO of LookSmart (IPO on Nasdaq) - two of Australia's earliest and largest internet successes. He was also a Group Manager at Microsoft in the US.","United States, California United States, San Francisco California United States, Americas, North America, Northwest, Bay Area",Research,[],,Angel Investors / HNW,[],0,,,,"[""Seed Round"", ""Early stage VC""]","Analytics, SaaS, Cybersecurity, Enterprise Software, Logistics, Health & Wellness (LOHAS), AI and Machine Learning, FinTech, PropTech, HealthTech",,,,https://www.linkedin.com/in/adrianvanzyl/,https://www.blumbergcapital.com/,,,,Adrian Vanzyl,adrianvanzyl@gmail.com,+65 9101 0589,"",https://www.linkedin.com/in/adrianvanzyl/,,https://www.blumbergcapital.com/,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
